g/products", "Geopolitics"]}}, {"id": "2069666609455677563", "url": "https://x.com/staunovo/status/2069666609455677563", "text": "A supertanker has been provisionally booked to transport oil from the Persian Gulf to India at a rate equivalent to almost nine times benchmark freight costs, an eye-watering price that reflects the shortage of available, empty vessels in the area.\n#oott https://t.co/3T5fS31Y7U", "time": "06:19", "author": "staunovo", "author_name": "Giovanni Staunovo🛢", "followers": 120883, "views": 18841, "likes": 156, "replies": 2, "retweets": 49, "quotes": 2, "bookmarks": 21, "labels": {"relevant": true, "price_sentiment": "Bullish", "emotional_sentiment": "Neutral", "topics": ["Tankers/shipping", "Supply outlook"]}}, {"id": "2069689934626091281", "url": "https://x.com/JavierBlas/status/2069689934626091281", "text": "US President Trump, all political theatre, has just discovered the refining (and marketing) margin. https://t.co/4u1q5Xz5qm", "time": "07:51", "author": "JavierBlas", "author_name": "Javier Blas", "followers": 393796, "views": 87473, "likes": 714, "replies": 75, "retweets": 131, "quotes": 23, "bookmarks": 38, "labels": {"relevant": true, "price_sentiment": "Neutral", "emotional_sentiment": "Negative", "topics": ["Refining/products"]}}, {"id": "2069721655773954465", "url": "https://x.com/JavierBlas/status/2069721655773954465", "text": "“… Physical crude oil cargoes are selling at discounts across the globe, changing trade flows as markets come under pressure from fast-rising Middle Eastern supply …”\n\nhttps://t.co/66ewWzq4v6", "time": "09:57", "author": "JavierBlas", "author_name": "Javier Blas", "followers": 393796, "views": 83701, "likes": 331, "replies": 19, "retweets": 110, "quotes": 14, "bookmarks": 41, "labels": {"relevant": true, "price_sentiment": "Bearish", "emotional_sentiment": "Neutral", "topics": ["Supply outlook", "Prices/technicals"]}}, {"id": "2069734111678247253", "url": "https://x.com/aeberman12/status/2069734111678247253", "text": "Reuters says oil markets are suddenly oversupplied.\n\nBut production hasn’t surged. Demand hasn’t collapsed.\n\nWhat’s changed is that trapped barrels are moving again and the Hormuz fear premium has evaporated.\n\nThat’s not a glut. It’s a traffic jam clearing. #Oil #OOTT #EnergyMarkets #Hormuz \n\nhttps:", "time": "10:47", "author": "aeberman12", "author_name": "Art Berman", "followers": 53616, "views": 29236, "likes": 351, "replies": 43, "retweets": 45, "quotes": 8, "bookmarks": 36, "labels": {"relevant": true, "price_sentiment": "Bearish", "emotional_sentiment": "Neutral", "topics": ["Supply outlook", "Geopolitics"]}}, {"id": "2069738278769574274", "url": "https://x.com/JavierBlas/status/2069738278769574274", "text": "China’s oil buying strike has sent the value of physical crude from Angola to a &gt;10-year low vs the Dated Brent benchmark. Beijing is typically a big importer of Angolan crude, but Chinese companies are now sellers, rather than buyers.", "time": "11:03", "author": "JavierBlas", "author_name": "Javier Blas", "followers": 393796, "views": 52079, "likes": 306, "replies": 9, "retweets": 45, "quotes": 7, "bookmarks": 29, "labels": {"relevant": true, "price_sentiment": "Bearish", "emotional_sentiment": "Neutral", "topics": ["China demand", "Demand outlook"]}}, {"id": "2069762119076049347", "url": "https://x.com/JavierBlas/status/2069762119076049347", "text": "Brent crude drops below $75 a barrel for the first time since the start of the U.S.-Iran war. \n\n📉⤵️ is Brent year-to-date (red line is Feb 27, 2026, the day before the conflict broke out) https://t.co/z6zkoIBm6k", "time": "12:38", "author": "JavierBlas", "author_name": "Javier Blas", "followers": 393796, "views": 33387, "likes": 187, "replies": 14, "retweets": 51, "quotes": 4, "bookmarks": 13, "labels": {"relevant": true, "price_sentiment": "Bearish", "emotional_sentiment": "Neutral", "topics": ["Prices/technicals"]}}, {"id": "2069767914597879837", "url": "https://x.com/DarioCpx/status/2069767914597879837", "text": "JustDarioDaily - Podcast\n\n⚠️ Hormuz Crisis Watch: Brent Crude Shorts at Extreme Levels 🎙️ \n\n#OOTT\n\nhttps://t.co/1Cf6GtJdQG", "time": "13:01", "author": "DarioCpx", "author_name": "JustDario", "followers": 113106, "views": 121413, "likes": 150, "replies": 27, "retweets": 17, "quotes": 1, "bookmarks": 21, "labels": {"relevant": true, "price_sentiment": "Bullish", "emotional_sentiment": "Neutral", "topics": ["Geopolitics", "Prices/technicals"]}}, {"id": "2069772583428301000", "url": "https://x.com/JavierBlas/status/2069772583428301000", "text": "Brent crude oil prompt time spread flips into contango.", "time": "13:20", "author": "JavierBlas", "author_name": "Javier Blas", "followers": 393796, "views": 45693, "likes": 190, "replies": 8, "retweets": 28, "quotes": 3, "bookmarks": 9, "labels": {"relevant": true, "price_sentiment": "Bearish", "emotional_sentiment": "Neutral", "topics": ["Prices/technicals"]}}, {"id": "2069779787594322420", "url": "https://x.com/JavierBlas/status/2069779787594322420", "text": "Is every day WTI crude oil stays above $65 still a great day?", "time": "13:48", "author": "JavierBlas", "author_name": "Javier Blas", "followers": 393796, "views": 52735, "likes": 187, "replies": 47, "retweets": 11, "quotes": 3, "bookmarks": 16, "labels": {"relevant": true, "price_sentiment": "Bearish", "emotional_sentiment": "Negative", "topics": ["Prices/technicals"]}}, {"id": "2069789247603962024", "url": "https://x.com/LVision_Trading/status/2069789247603962024", "text": "IMO: hundreds of vessels can now leave the Persian Gulf via Hormuz\n\nMarkets: oil bath. $73.5\n\nMe: count the ducklings. 89 crude tankers. ~135M bbls max - indulge in every pleasure.\n\nExits outpacing entries today.\n\nWhen the last duckling leaves what happens?\n\n$OIL #OOTT NFA", "time": "14:26", "author": "LVision_Trading", "author_name": "Laman", "followers": 1924, "views": 16767, "likes": 146, "replies": 18, "retweets": 13, "quotes": 3, "bookmarks": 16, "labels": {"relevant": true, "price_sentiment": "Bullish", "emotional_sentiment": "Positive", "topics": ["Tankers/shipping", "Supply outlook"]}}, {"id": "2069806840695967988", "url": "https://x.com/a4_alpha/status/2069806840695967988", "text": "TMF, the numbers do not lie. China may not be a buyer today but demand is not falling and inventories are drawing. I expect a united front to talk #energy prices lower as it is a risk to the global economy. This is an opportunity for those who see it.\n\nThank you #OOTT #EFT #COM", "time": "15:36", "author": "a4_alpha", "author_name": "A4Alpha", "followers": 7996, "views": 84268, "likes": 317, "replies": 5, "retweets": 9, "quotes": 2, "bookmarks": 77, "labels": {"relevant": true, "price_sentiment": "Bullish", "emotional_sentiment": "Positive", "topics": ["Demand outlook", "US inventories"]}}, {"id": "2069811106177229025", "url": "https://x.com/TankerTrackers/status/2069811106177229025", "text": "Iran has exported 40 million barrels of crude oil since 2026-06-15. Exactly half of that amount shipped out in a single day; which was last Friday (2026-06-19).\n\n#OOTT #IranWar #Tankers", "time": "15:53", "author": "TankerTrackers", "author_name": "TankerTrackers.com, Inc.", "followers": 227035, "views": 168737, "likes": 402, "replies": 14, "retweets": 96, "quotes": 33, "bookmarks": 45, "labels": {"relevant": true, "price_sentiment": "Bearish", "emotional_sentiment": "Neutral", "topics": ["Iran", "Tankers/shipping"]}}, {"id": "2069870571874091150", "url": "https://x.com/JavierBlas/status/2069870571874091150", "text": "Key parts of the oil market are suddenly awash in supply, as a stream of cargoes out of the Strait of Hormuz accelerates after the US-Iran agreement to open the waterway. https://t.co/wtgG5GtvwF", "time": "19:49", "author": "JavierBlas", "author_name": "Javier Blas", "followers": 393796, "views": 37881, "likes": 203, "replies": 24, "retweets": 46, "quotes": 6, "bookmarks": 32, "labels": {"relevant": true, "price_sentiment": "Bearish", "emotional_sentiment": "Neutral", "topics": ["Supply outlook", "Tankers/shipping", "Iran"]}}, {"id": "2069925230655471731", "url": "https://x.com/aeberman12/status/2069925230655471731", "text": "Oil prices are back near pre-war levels\n\nBut inventories keep falling toward record lows\n\nEveryone is watching barrels leaving Hormuz\n\nFar fewer are watching the barrels going back in\n\nThe IRGC can count barrels too\n\n#OOTT #Oil #Hormuz #Energy #Geopolitics", "time": "23:26", "author": "aeberman12", "author_name": "Art Berman", "followers": 53616, "views": 14629, "likes": 192, "replies": 10, "retweets": 28, "quotes": 3, "bookmarks": 14, "labels": {"relevant": true, "price_sentiment": "Bullish", "emotional_sentiment": "Neutral", "topics": ["US inventories", "Geopolitics"]}}], "top_authors_by_tweets": [{"username": "staunovo", "name": "Giovanni Staunovo🛢", "followers": 120883, "tweets": 38, "views": 197835, "likes": 646}, {"username": "ZmansEnrgyBrain", "name": "Z4 Energy Research", "followers": 11920, "tweets": 14, "views": 26555, "likes": 139}, {"username": "aeberman12", "name": "Art Berman", "followers": 53616, "tweets": 8, "views": 66888, "likes": 821}, {"username": "CDCapMan", "name": "CD Capital Management", "followers": 164, "tweets": 8, "views": 1818, "likes": 18}, {"username": "JavierBlas", "name": "Javier Blas", "followers": 393796, "tweets": 7, "views": 392949, "likes": 2118}], "top_authors_by_views": [{"username": "JavierBlas", "name": "Javier Blas", "followers": 393796, "tweets": 7, "views": 392949, "likes": 2118}, {"username": "staunovo", "name": "Giovanni Staunovo🛢", "followers": 120883, "tweets": 38, "views": 197835, "likes": 646}, {"username": "TankerTrackers", "name": "TankerTrackers.com, Inc.", "followers": 227035, "tweets": 1, "views": 168737, "likes": 402}, {"username": "DarioCpx", "name": "JustDario", "followers": 113106, "tweets": 1, "views": 121413, "likes": 150}, {"username": "a4_alpha", "name": "A4Alpha", "followers"